1
00:00:11,179 --> 00:00:13,347
Man: Folks say life is a song.

2
00:00:13,381 --> 00:00:18,186
For some, that means a ditty;
for others, a dirge.

3
00:00:18,219 --> 00:00:24,258
But at the holiday season,
we all sing a carol...

4
00:00:38,139 --> 00:00:40,541
* Tell me a tale
about Christmas *

5
00:00:40,574 --> 00:00:43,344
* That's brimming with fun
and good cheer *

6
00:00:43,377 --> 00:00:46,147
* Tell me a tale
to bring laughter *

7
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:48,716
* And maybe the hint
of a tear *

8
00:00:48,749 --> 00:00:51,652
* Tell me a tale
 of a miser *

9
00:00:51,685 --> 00:00:54,522
* Who spoils every joy
that he can *

10
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:57,291
* Can he get older and wiser?

11
00:00:57,325 --> 00:01:00,328
* Will he become a good man?

12
00:01:00,361 --> 00:01:03,231
* Christmas stories

13
00:01:03,264 --> 00:01:06,334
* What warm memories
they bring *

14
00:01:06,367 --> 00:01:09,203
* Christmas carols

15
00:01:09,237 --> 00:01:11,239
* Make me want to sing

16
00:01:11,272 --> 00:01:14,642
* Tra la la
la la la la la *

17
00:01:14,675 --> 00:01:16,644
* Tra la la la la la la

18
00:01:16,677 --> 00:01:22,316
* Tra la la
la la la la la la *

19
00:01:22,350 --> 00:01:24,652
* Sing me a song
full of wonder *

20
00:01:24,685 --> 00:01:27,855
* Like snow from
the heavens above *

21
00:01:27,888 --> 00:01:32,760
* Sing me a song
about Christmas *

22
00:01:32,793 --> 00:01:35,129
* Sing me a song

23
00:01:35,163 --> 00:01:41,235
* Of love

24
00:01:45,206 --> 00:01:47,175
[clock ticking]

25
00:01:47,208 --> 00:01:49,777
[humming]

26
00:01:54,315 --> 00:01:59,753
[clock chiming]

27
00:02:02,856 --> 00:02:05,293
Ohhh!

28
00:02:05,326 --> 00:02:07,728
Brr!

29
00:02:19,207 --> 00:02:21,375
I'm gonna
get you again!

30
00:02:21,409 --> 00:02:22,843
Oh, no, you won't!

31
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:25,579
Ha ha ha!

32
00:02:26,447 --> 00:02:28,416
Ah...

33
00:02:48,536 --> 00:02:49,903
[humming]

34
00:02:49,937 --> 00:02:52,673
[clock ticking]

35
00:02:53,574 --> 00:02:54,575
...Sixpence.

36
00:02:54,608 --> 00:02:57,411
Younger man:
* Christmas

37
00:02:57,445 --> 00:02:58,546
Cratchit!

38
00:02:58,579 --> 00:03:01,949
Sorry, Mr. Scrooge.

39
00:03:03,384 --> 00:03:05,719
[snoring]

40
00:03:05,753 --> 00:03:06,754
Debit!

41
00:03:06,787 --> 00:03:08,356
Uh...

42
00:03:13,561 --> 00:03:18,366
[growling and sniffing]

43
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:20,568
[snarling]

44
00:03:20,601 --> 00:03:22,570
Uh! Ohhh...

45
00:03:23,571 --> 00:03:24,938
Ahh! Ahh!

46
00:03:24,972 --> 00:03:28,842
[ruff ruff
ruff ruff ruff]

47
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,986
Excuse me, guv. Aah!

48
00:03:39,019 --> 00:03:40,354
[ruff ruff]

49
00:03:40,388 --> 00:03:42,523
Beat it, brat!

50
00:03:42,556 --> 00:03:44,392
Grr!

51
00:03:44,425 --> 00:03:46,560
[gasps]

52
00:03:55,969 --> 00:03:59,039
Cratchit,
go fetch that coal!

53
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:02,242
Yes, Mr. Scrooge.

54
00:04:05,012 --> 00:04:06,614
Excuse me, sir.

55
00:04:06,647 --> 00:04:10,651
A merry Christmas,
Uncle Ebenezer!

56
00:04:12,686 --> 00:04:16,256
Bah! Humbug!

57
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:18,492
[grr]

58
00:04:18,526 --> 00:04:19,760
[ruff ruff]

59
00:04:19,793 --> 00:04:20,994
Christmas a humbug?

60
00:04:21,028 --> 00:04:23,297
Well, you don't
mean that.

61
00:04:23,331 --> 00:04:24,332
I do.

62
00:04:24,365 --> 00:04:28,636
Merry Christmas?
What right have you
to be merry?

63
00:04:28,669 --> 00:04:29,903
You're poor enough.

64
00:04:29,937 --> 00:04:31,872
What right have you
to be grumpy?

65
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:33,073
You're rich enough.

66
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:37,945
Yes, rich enough
to realize Christmas
is a time for fools...

67
00:04:37,978 --> 00:04:42,416
Finding themselves
a year older and not
an hour richer.

68
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:43,951
If I had my way,

69
00:04:43,984 --> 00:04:45,152
every numskull
who goes about

70
00:04:45,185 --> 00:04:50,057
spouting "merry Christmas"
should be stuffed like a turkey,

71
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:55,763
buried with a stake of holly
through his heart!

72
00:04:56,597 --> 00:04:57,965
Uncle!

73
00:04:57,998 --> 00:04:59,032
Nephew!

74
00:04:59,066 --> 00:05:01,802
Keep Christmas
in your own way

75
00:05:01,835 --> 00:05:03,537
and let me
keep it in mine.

76
00:05:03,571 --> 00:05:07,575
Keep it?
But you don't keep it.

77
00:05:07,608 --> 00:05:08,576
No. I keep busy,

78
00:05:08,609 --> 00:05:12,380
especially
at this wasteful
time of year.

79
00:05:12,413 --> 00:05:13,581
Wasteful?

80
00:05:13,614 --> 00:05:16,584
Well, I've always
thought of Christmas
as a rewarding time.

81
00:05:16,617 --> 00:05:19,953
Even putting aside
its sacred name and origin,

82
00:05:19,987 --> 00:05:23,424
Christmas is still
a joyous, wonderful season,

83
00:05:23,457 --> 00:05:26,026
the only time
in the whole year

84
00:05:26,059 --> 00:05:30,664
when folks seem to open
their hearts and treat
strangers as friends,

85
00:05:30,698 --> 00:05:34,968
and therefore, Uncle,
though it's never put
silver in my pocket,

86
00:05:35,002 --> 00:05:39,673
I say god bless Christmas!

87
00:05:39,707 --> 00:05:41,975
[squeaking]

88
00:05:43,076 --> 00:05:45,579
Ahhh!

89
00:05:47,147 --> 00:05:49,517
Grr!

90
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:52,119
Bah! Humbug!

91
00:05:53,821 --> 00:05:56,657
[ruff ruff]

92
00:05:58,726 --> 00:06:01,128
[whining]

93
00:06:05,933 --> 00:06:10,037
Give us a smile, Uncle.
Tomorrow is Christmas.

94
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:11,939
Good afternoon.

95
00:06:11,972 --> 00:06:14,642
Well, have dinner
with my wife and me.

96
00:06:14,675 --> 00:06:17,010
Good afternoon.

97
00:06:17,044 --> 00:06:18,078
Very well.

98
00:06:18,111 --> 00:06:19,747
If you want to be
miserable, fine,

99
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:23,917
but I'll hang on
to my holiday spirit
to the last.

100
00:06:24,985 --> 00:06:26,454
So merry Christmas, Uncle.

101
00:06:26,487 --> 00:06:29,590
Good afternoon!

102
00:06:29,623 --> 00:06:30,824
Ha ha ha!

103
00:06:30,858 --> 00:06:32,926
And a happy new year!

104
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:34,995
Good afternoon!

105
00:06:38,766 --> 00:06:40,167
Man:
Scrooge & Marley's,
yes?

106
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:44,572
Have I the pleasure of
addressing Mr. Scrooge
or Mr. Marley?

107
00:06:44,605 --> 00:06:51,445
Mr. Marley
died 7 years ago
this very night.

108
00:06:51,479 --> 00:06:52,780
Oh, dear!

109
00:06:52,813 --> 00:06:54,014
However,
we have no doubt

110
00:06:54,047 --> 00:06:58,852
your generosity
matches that of your
deceased partner's, hmm?

111
00:06:58,886 --> 00:07:01,955
Here you are,
Mr. Scrooge.

112
00:07:03,123 --> 00:07:05,726
That's only 5 lumps.

113
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:07,194
Where's the sixth?

114
00:07:07,227 --> 00:07:09,062
The snow, sir.

115
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:13,901
Back to work!
Coal's not cheap,
you know.

116
00:07:16,236 --> 00:07:18,606
Uh, generosity, yes.

117
00:07:18,639 --> 00:07:20,040
Uh, at this
festive season,

118
00:07:20,073 --> 00:07:23,243
it is compassionate
to provide for the poor
and destitute,

119
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:26,680
who suffer greatly
at this time.

120
00:07:29,683 --> 00:07:33,654
What shall I
put you down for?

121
00:07:35,689 --> 00:07:36,690
Huh?

122
00:07:36,724 --> 00:07:38,091
Nothing!

123
00:07:38,692 --> 00:07:41,061
Ah! You wish
to be anonymous!

124
00:07:41,094 --> 00:07:44,131
I wish to be
left alone!

125
00:07:44,164 --> 00:07:46,033
I don't make merry
at Christmas,

126
00:07:46,066 --> 00:07:50,103
and I can't afford
to make idle people
merry!

127
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:52,806
But surely, sir--

128
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:53,741
I do my share.

129
00:07:53,774 --> 00:07:57,010
My taxes pay for
the prisons and workhouses,

130
00:07:57,044 --> 00:08:01,048
and those
who are badly off
should go there!

131
00:08:01,081 --> 00:08:02,249
But many
would rather die.

132
00:08:02,282 --> 00:08:07,821
Then they should do it
and decrease
the surplus population.

133
00:08:07,855 --> 00:08:12,960
But, sir,
thousands are in need
of simple comforts.

134
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:17,297
Huh!
It's not my business,
gentlemen.

135
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:19,066
Good afternoon.

136
00:08:19,099 --> 00:08:21,769
Uh, but,
Mr. Scrooge--

137
00:08:21,802 --> 00:08:23,537
Scrooge: Debit!

138
00:08:23,571 --> 00:08:25,505
[snarling]

139
00:08:26,073 --> 00:08:29,076
[gasping]
[gasping]

140
00:08:32,713 --> 00:08:35,248
Ooh!

141
00:08:39,052 --> 00:08:40,588
[ptooey]

142
00:08:40,621 --> 00:08:42,222
[grr]

143
00:08:42,255 --> 00:08:44,892
[clock chiming]

144
00:08:51,865 --> 00:08:53,901
[knock on door]

145
00:08:55,703 --> 00:08:57,705
Hello?

146
00:08:58,806 --> 00:09:01,041
Huh! Bleh!
Beat it, beggar!

147
00:09:01,074 --> 00:09:02,042
Cratchit: No!

148
00:09:02,075 --> 00:09:05,178
No, sir.
This is my son Tim.

149
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:08,148
Oh. You have
a family? Hmm?

150
00:09:08,181 --> 00:09:11,619
He's awfully, uh...

151
00:09:11,652 --> 00:09:13,654
Tiny.

152
00:09:13,687 --> 00:09:15,923
Yes. Yes, he is.

153
00:09:15,956 --> 00:09:17,024
He's our tiny Tim.

154
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:21,929
Hmm. You'll want
all day off tomorrow,
I suppose.

155
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:25,999
If it's convenient, sir.

156
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,101
It's not
convenient...

157
00:09:28,135 --> 00:09:29,136
Hee hee hee!

158
00:09:29,169 --> 00:09:30,370
And it's
not fair.

159
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:35,142
If I docked you for it,
you'd feel cheated,
I imagine.

160
00:09:35,175 --> 00:09:38,746
And yet you don't
think me cheated

161
00:09:38,779 --> 00:09:41,248
when I pay a day's wages
for no work.

162
00:09:41,281 --> 00:09:43,817
It is only
once a year, sir.

163
00:09:43,851 --> 00:09:47,921
A poor excuse for
picking my pocket
every december the 25th!

164
00:09:47,955 --> 00:09:52,092
But I suppose
I've got to give you
the whole day.

165
00:09:52,125 --> 00:09:55,362
Just be here
an hour earlier
next morning.

166
00:09:55,395 --> 00:09:56,797
Yes, sir.

167
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:58,131
Thank you, sir.

168
00:09:58,165 --> 00:09:59,700
And a very merry...

169
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:00,768
Um...

170
00:10:00,801 --> 00:10:03,036
Merry evening, sir.

171
00:10:03,070 --> 00:10:04,337
Come, son.

172
00:10:04,371 --> 00:10:07,641
He likes me,
father.

173
00:10:07,675 --> 00:10:08,642
Huh?

174
00:10:08,676 --> 00:10:12,179
Scrooge: Debit!

175
00:10:14,114 --> 00:10:19,319
Get the light,
you liability.

176
00:11:01,394 --> 00:11:02,362
Whee!

177
00:11:02,395 --> 00:11:04,865
Ha ha ha!

178
00:11:11,271 --> 00:11:13,406
Tim: Go, horsy!

179
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,743
Ha ha ha!

180
00:11:18,111 --> 00:11:21,148
[debit panting
and snorting]

181
00:11:22,349 --> 00:11:23,717
Scrooge: Debit!

182
00:11:23,751 --> 00:11:25,018
Huh?

183
00:11:25,052 --> 00:11:27,687
[grr]

184
00:11:34,862 --> 00:11:40,100
That old villain's
cold as ice, isn't he?

185
00:11:45,105 --> 00:11:46,774
[children oohing and ahing]

186
00:11:46,807 --> 00:11:49,076
Look at the size
of that turkey.

187
00:11:49,109 --> 00:11:51,078
Doesn't it
look good?

188
00:11:51,111 --> 00:11:53,013
Debit!

189
00:11:56,984 --> 00:12:00,053
[laughter and piano music
from inside]

190
00:12:10,898 --> 00:12:12,966
What'll it be,
ducky?

191
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,002
Hash for me.
Scraps for my dog.

192
00:12:15,035 --> 00:12:17,504
And be quick
about it.

193
00:12:22,876 --> 00:12:24,845
Every day
the same thing--

194
00:12:24,878 --> 00:12:26,146
cheapest meal
on the menu!

195
00:12:26,179 --> 00:12:30,984
When he could afford
a feast every night,
the old skinflint.

196
00:12:31,018 --> 00:12:36,056
Oh, well, can't let him
ruin our holiday,
now, can we?

197
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:38,025
Ha ha ha!

198
00:12:39,893 --> 00:12:41,829
* It's Christmastime
at last *

199
00:12:41,862 --> 00:12:43,030
* Revellers, prepare

200
00:12:43,063 --> 00:12:46,466
* Can't you feel a blast of
fresh excitement in the air? *

201
00:12:46,499 --> 00:12:48,135
* The wreath
is out of hock *

202
00:12:48,168 --> 00:12:49,436
* Holly's in the hall

203
00:12:49,469 --> 00:12:52,539
* But take some stock before you
pin that stocking to the wall *

204
00:12:52,572 --> 00:12:56,076
* Random acts of kindness,
random acts of kindness *

205
00:12:56,109 --> 00:12:59,279
* Have you spread your share
of merry Christmas cheer? *

206
00:12:59,312 --> 00:13:01,114
* Perform an act
of kindness? *

207
00:13:01,148 --> 00:13:05,485
* Random acts of kindness,
more than once a year *

208
00:13:05,518 --> 00:13:06,486
For example...

209
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:07,988
Offering
a scone.

210
00:13:08,021 --> 00:13:09,189
Springing
for the nog!

211
00:13:09,222 --> 00:13:12,225
* Throwing out the bone to throw
a banquet for the dog *

212
00:13:12,259 --> 00:13:15,462
* Freshening a drink,
sharing what you've earned *

213
00:13:15,495 --> 00:13:19,099
Man: * Giving without thinking
that it's got to be returned *

214
00:13:19,132 --> 00:13:21,001
All:
* Random acts of kindness

215
00:13:21,034 --> 00:13:22,102
* Random acts
of kindness *

216
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:25,605
Waitress: * Preferably
performed with anonymity *

217
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:26,974
* It's your
yuletide duty *

218
00:13:27,007 --> 00:13:28,976
* Commit
some senseless beauty *

219
00:13:29,009 --> 00:13:32,112
* Palm some off on me

220
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:35,482
All: * Love makes
giving so pleasing *

221
00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:38,118
* 'Tis the seasonal way

222
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:41,588
* Still the biggest trick
is getting it to stick *

223
00:13:41,621 --> 00:13:45,492
* After Christmas day

224
00:13:45,525 --> 00:13:47,995
Oh, bah! Humbug!

225
00:13:48,028 --> 00:13:51,198
* Give a bum a bob,
he'll go buy a pint of ale *

226
00:13:51,231 --> 00:13:52,632
* Then he'll borrow,
beg, and rob you *

227
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:54,034
* And at best,
end up in jail *

228
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:57,871
* When he's been released,
who'll come breaking
through your door? *

229
00:13:57,905 --> 00:14:01,041
* That's what good
your beastly brand
of charity is for *

230
00:14:01,074 --> 00:14:03,143
* Random acts of kindness,
random acts-- *

231
00:14:03,176 --> 00:14:05,913
* You'll find no good deed
goes unpunished *

232
00:14:05,946 --> 00:14:07,881
* And no crook
goes straight *

233
00:14:07,915 --> 00:14:08,982
* Random sacrifices

234
00:14:09,016 --> 00:14:14,054
* Falsely playing nice is
man's most hateful trait *

235
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:17,490
* See the Christmas snow
falling *

236
00:14:17,524 --> 00:14:20,293
* Don't it tug
at your heart? *

237
00:14:20,327 --> 00:14:23,997
* While you're in this phase,
better change your ways *

238
00:14:24,031 --> 00:14:27,134
* Now's the time to start

239
00:14:27,167 --> 00:14:28,902
Bah! Humbug!

240
00:14:28,936 --> 00:14:30,904
All:
* Random acts of kindness

241
00:14:30,938 --> 00:14:32,139
* Random acts
of kindness *

242
00:14:32,172 --> 00:14:35,976
Waitress: * Just in case it's
you who ends up on the ground *

243
00:14:36,009 --> 00:14:38,445
All:
* Kindly ways and fandom,
kindly acts at random *

244
00:14:38,478 --> 00:14:44,584
* Make the world go round

245
00:14:44,617 --> 00:14:49,656
Waitress, here's the only tip
you'll be getting from me:

246
00:14:49,689 --> 00:14:54,061
Find a new chef.
Your hash
isn't fit for a dog.

247
00:14:54,094 --> 00:14:55,262
Ha ha ha!

248
00:14:55,295 --> 00:14:58,265
[everybody laughing]

249
00:15:10,443 --> 00:15:14,014
[baby crying]

250
00:15:16,683 --> 00:15:18,518
Please, sir.

251
00:15:18,551 --> 00:15:21,121
[baby cries]

252
00:15:36,103 --> 00:15:38,538
[gasps]

253
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,542
Jacob?

254
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:44,544
Boo!

255
00:15:44,577 --> 00:15:45,712
[gasps]

256
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:48,415
Argh!

257
00:15:51,318 --> 00:15:53,987
Wretched animal!

258
00:16:13,773 --> 00:16:16,109
[debit whines]

259
00:16:17,210 --> 00:16:19,979
Stupid dog.

260
00:16:26,253 --> 00:16:28,021
[wind blows]

261
00:16:28,055 --> 00:16:30,057
[debit whimpers]

262
00:16:34,494 --> 00:16:39,466
Eeerie male voice:
Ebenezer Scrooge.

263
00:16:39,499 --> 00:16:41,034
Huh?

264
00:16:42,069 --> 00:16:44,003
[gasps]

265
00:16:59,419 --> 00:17:01,421
Humbug!

266
00:17:15,168 --> 00:17:17,570
[snoring]

267
00:17:19,739 --> 00:17:23,110
[wind blows]

268
00:17:31,318 --> 00:17:33,553
Scrooge.

269
00:17:33,586 --> 00:17:35,555
Huh? Ah!

270
00:17:41,528 --> 00:17:45,532
Scrooge.

271
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:49,469
Go away!
I won't believe it.

272
00:17:49,502 --> 00:17:51,571
[ruff ruff]

273
00:17:51,604 --> 00:17:55,375
Shut up! It's nothing!

274
00:18:11,824 --> 00:18:16,296
Bah! Old fool! You're
acting like a dunderhead!

275
00:18:16,329 --> 00:18:19,399
No such thing as spirits!

276
00:18:19,432 --> 00:18:21,568
[yelps]

277
00:18:32,179 --> 00:18:35,114
What is it, debit?

278
00:18:38,185 --> 00:18:40,153
[whimpering]

279
00:18:53,366 --> 00:18:58,871
Ebenezer Scrooge!

280
00:18:58,905 --> 00:19:01,574
Sic him!

281
00:19:07,580 --> 00:19:09,182
[yelps]

282
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:13,853
Look at me,
Ebenezer!

283
00:19:13,886 --> 00:19:18,858
In life I was
your partner...

284
00:19:18,891 --> 00:19:23,196
Jacob Marley.

285
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:26,833
I heard you had
no heart, Jacob.

286
00:19:26,866 --> 00:19:28,568
Now I see it's true.

287
00:19:28,601 --> 00:19:32,939
So you believe
in me, then.

288
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:34,807
I don't.

289
00:19:34,841 --> 00:19:38,711
You're probably just
some undigested food--

290
00:19:38,745 --> 00:19:41,781
some bad beef
or a blob of mustard.

291
00:19:41,814 --> 00:19:45,652
There's more of gravy
than of grave about you.

292
00:19:45,685 --> 00:19:49,188
[shouting angrily]

293
00:19:53,926 --> 00:19:55,928
Ahh!

294
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:05,004
Mercy! Why do
you haunt me?

295
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:08,275
I've come
to warn you...

296
00:20:08,308 --> 00:20:12,445
To spare you my fate.

297
00:20:12,812 --> 00:20:14,981
You mean...All this...

298
00:20:15,014 --> 00:20:16,416
Hardware?

299
00:20:16,449 --> 00:20:20,753
I wear the chain
I forged in life.

300
00:20:20,787 --> 00:20:23,590
I made it
link by link.

301
00:20:23,623 --> 00:20:28,561
This link was when
I evicted those orphans,

302
00:20:28,595 --> 00:20:32,632
and here's when I
cheated old Mrs. Avery.

303
00:20:32,665 --> 00:20:37,970
And your chain
was this long and heavy
7 years ago!

304
00:20:38,004 --> 00:20:43,576
You should see it
now, Ebenezer.

305
00:20:44,377 --> 00:20:46,546
I can't see a chain!

306
00:20:46,579 --> 00:20:48,715
I can!

307
00:20:48,748 --> 00:20:51,284
And it is
a monstrous one!

308
00:20:51,318 --> 00:20:57,424
It is our human duty
to walk among
our neighbors

309
00:20:57,457 --> 00:20:59,692
and do good.

310
00:20:59,726 --> 00:21:03,596
If we fail to do this
while we're alive,

311
00:21:03,630 --> 00:21:09,436
then we're doomed
to do it after death.

312
00:21:09,469 --> 00:21:10,803
Look!

313
00:21:10,837 --> 00:21:13,840
See that poor woman?

314
00:21:13,873 --> 00:21:15,908
It's not
my business.

315
00:21:15,942 --> 00:21:20,647
Mankind is
our business.

316
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,717
[baby whimpering]

317
00:21:24,751 --> 00:21:25,718
Please.

318
00:21:25,752 --> 00:21:28,688
Take this
for the baby.

319
00:21:28,721 --> 00:21:34,961
Marley: By the time
we realize we must
help one another,

320
00:21:34,994 --> 00:21:37,630
it is usually too late.

321
00:21:37,664 --> 00:21:44,537
When we're dead,
we can no longer do
any earthly good.

322
00:21:44,571 --> 00:21:46,573
But I have good news!

323
00:21:46,606 --> 00:21:50,109
Tonight,
on the anniversary
of my death,

324
00:21:50,142 --> 00:21:56,549
I've been given
the opportunity to
warn you, Scrooge.

325
00:21:56,583 --> 00:22:01,688
Perhaps you can
escape my fate.

326
00:22:01,721 --> 00:22:02,789
Really?

327
00:22:02,822 --> 00:22:06,025
You simply visit me,
and then everything's
all right?

328
00:22:06,058 --> 00:22:09,061
Almost. You'll also be
haunted by 3 spirits.

329
00:22:15,134 --> 00:22:16,369
No deal.

330
00:22:16,403 --> 00:22:22,975
Without their visits,
you cannot hope
to break your chains.

331
00:22:23,009 --> 00:22:25,878
I don't care, Jacob!
I like chains!

332
00:22:25,912 --> 00:22:27,880
No ghosts,
you hear me?!

333
00:22:27,914 --> 00:22:31,751
Expect the first when
the bell tolls 1:00.

334
00:22:42,929 --> 00:22:45,965
No ghosts!

335
00:22:49,969 --> 00:22:52,872
Bah! Humbug!

336
00:22:53,906 --> 00:22:57,043
[ticking]

337
00:22:57,944 --> 00:22:59,512
[chimes]

338
00:23:02,882 --> 00:23:05,918
[snoring]

339
00:23:08,988 --> 00:23:11,023
[thunderous noise]

340
00:23:18,598 --> 00:23:21,200
[giggling]

341
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:24,937
Mornin',
Ebenezer Scrooge.

342
00:23:24,971 --> 00:23:27,907
[growls]

343
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:28,908
Boo!

344
00:23:28,941 --> 00:23:30,643
[yelps]

345
00:23:31,010 --> 00:23:33,680
[giggling]

346
00:23:34,914 --> 00:23:36,683
[thud]
Aah!

347
00:23:36,716 --> 00:23:38,685
Oww!

348
00:23:39,151 --> 00:23:43,890
Are--are you
the first spirit
Jacob talked about?

349
00:23:43,923 --> 00:23:48,861
Spot on, guvnor!
I'm the ghost
of Christmas past.

350
00:23:48,895 --> 00:23:50,463
Long past?

351
00:23:50,497 --> 00:23:55,668
No. Your past.
Follow me.

352
00:23:56,168 --> 00:23:59,171
It's for
your own good.

353
00:23:59,806 --> 00:24:01,508
A night
of unbroken sleep

354
00:24:01,541 --> 00:24:05,512
would be better
for my good than this.

355
00:24:06,646 --> 00:24:09,048
Shuffle your stumps,
Scrooge!

356
00:24:10,082 --> 00:24:11,918
[gasps]

357
00:24:14,887 --> 00:24:19,225
I'm not made of
mist and moonlight
like you.

358
00:24:19,258 --> 00:24:22,261
I'll fall! No!

359
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:24,163
[ruff ruff ruff]

360
00:24:24,196 --> 00:24:25,932
Debit, help!

361
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:29,536
[ruff ruff ruff]

362
00:24:29,569 --> 00:24:31,738
[growling]

363
00:24:33,005 --> 00:24:34,841
Stop fussing!

364
00:24:34,874 --> 00:24:38,945
You're no help,
debit! Let go!

365
00:24:40,012 --> 00:24:42,181
Huh-uh! Uh-uh!

366
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:57,697
I...I was a boy here.

367
00:24:57,730 --> 00:25:02,001
Aye, guvnor.
This here was your
boarding school.

368
00:25:02,034 --> 00:25:03,703
Do you recollect
the way?

369
00:25:03,736 --> 00:25:08,007
Recollect it? I could
walk it blindfold.

370
00:25:38,004 --> 00:25:39,872
[inhales deeply]

371
00:25:39,906 --> 00:25:44,143
Ah, chalk dust
and wood smoke.

372
00:25:44,176 --> 00:25:46,746
[sniffing]

373
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:57,690
[growling]

374
00:26:01,060 --> 00:26:03,029
[yelps]

375
00:26:03,062 --> 00:26:04,764
[chuckles]

376
00:26:04,797 --> 00:26:07,099
What you see are
but shadows

377
00:26:07,133 --> 00:26:09,969
of the things
that have been.

378
00:26:10,002 --> 00:26:12,304
They can't see
of us.

379
00:26:12,338 --> 00:26:13,973
Oh. Of course.

380
00:26:14,006 --> 00:26:18,010
Why didn't you think
of that, you twit?

381
00:26:20,713 --> 00:26:25,952
Spirit: A small boy,
all alone, neglected
by his friends,

382
00:26:25,985 --> 00:26:29,656
rejected by the father
what left him here.

383
00:26:29,689 --> 00:26:32,391
It...It is...

384
00:26:32,424 --> 00:26:34,026
Me.

385
00:26:34,060 --> 00:26:36,863
Poor forgotten boy.

386
00:26:36,896 --> 00:26:42,969
He--I--was never invited
home for the holidays.

387
00:26:43,002 --> 00:26:47,640
Alone...Stranded.

388
00:26:47,674 --> 00:26:48,975
[sniffling]

389
00:26:49,008 --> 00:26:50,677
I wish...

390
00:26:50,710 --> 00:26:52,411
What's the matter, eh?

391
00:26:52,444 --> 00:26:56,115
There was a boy
at my door last night.

392
00:26:56,148 --> 00:26:59,952
Perhaps I should have
given him something.
That's all.

393
00:26:59,986 --> 00:27:04,991
You did, guv.
A fistful of coal!

394
00:27:10,963 --> 00:27:15,401
Scrooge: It's
Robinson Crusoe! Yes!

395
00:27:15,434 --> 00:27:18,004
I remember this day.

396
00:27:18,037 --> 00:27:20,940
He was my favorite
storybook character.

397
00:27:20,973 --> 00:27:26,145
Blimey! You've been visited
by spirits before.

398
00:27:26,178 --> 00:27:29,816
Don't mock me, shade.

399
00:27:40,026 --> 00:27:44,330
* Everyone's gone
but the cat *

400
00:27:44,363 --> 00:27:48,467
* Once again
I'm all alone *

401
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:52,939
* But I need
all my shadows *

402
00:27:52,972 --> 00:27:57,977
* To show them
I'm fine on my own *

403
00:28:04,516 --> 00:28:06,685
[reowr]

404
00:28:08,054 --> 00:28:10,923
* I'll slay the beast

405
00:28:10,957 --> 00:28:13,993
* I'll bring the feast

406
00:28:14,026 --> 00:28:19,031
* I'll throw a carnival
with 40 clowns at least *

407
00:28:22,501 --> 00:28:25,437
* I'll ride a whale

408
00:28:25,471 --> 00:28:29,508
* I'll find the grail

409
00:28:29,541 --> 00:28:31,443
* I'll be a matador

410
00:28:31,477 --> 00:28:36,415
* What's more, I'll live
to tell the tale *

411
00:28:36,448 --> 00:28:39,986
* Like arthur
on his throne *

412
00:28:40,019 --> 00:28:43,522
* I won't be alone

413
00:28:43,555 --> 00:28:48,761
* Once I pull the sword
out of the stone *

414
00:28:51,363 --> 00:28:55,167
* Not sad at all

415
00:28:55,201 --> 00:28:58,237
* Up on the wall

416
00:28:58,270 --> 00:29:05,011
* See all my friends
when shadows fall *

417
00:29:05,044 --> 00:29:08,948
* But then as
the firelight dies *

418
00:29:08,981 --> 00:29:13,119
* I can see
with my own eyes *

419
00:29:13,152 --> 00:29:16,823
* No friends at all

420
00:29:16,856 --> 00:29:19,325
* When shadows

421
00:29:19,358 --> 00:29:25,764
* Fall

422
00:29:29,969 --> 00:29:33,840
Spirit: Let's see
another Christmas.

423
00:29:35,942 --> 00:29:39,045
Bah! Humbug!

424
00:29:47,053 --> 00:29:48,855
[sighs]

425
00:29:48,888 --> 00:29:53,059
So many lonely
Christmases.

426
00:29:53,092 --> 00:29:56,195
Right,
but not this one.

427
00:29:56,228 --> 00:29:58,898
[giggling]
Ebby!

428
00:29:58,931 --> 00:29:59,899
Fan!

429
00:29:59,932 --> 00:30:01,934
Fan?

430
00:30:04,403 --> 00:30:05,337
My little sister.

431
00:30:05,371 --> 00:30:08,307
I've come to bring
you home, dear brother.

432
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:09,508
Home?

433
00:30:09,541 --> 00:30:11,010
But father...

434
00:30:11,043 --> 00:30:12,544
Oh, pooh on father.

435
00:30:12,578 --> 00:30:14,513
I'm inviting you.
We're family,

436
00:30:14,546 --> 00:30:17,950
and I told father
I want you at home!

437
00:30:17,984 --> 00:30:19,986
Good old fan!

438
00:30:20,019 --> 00:30:21,287
Lovely fan.

439
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:25,524
Such a large heart for
such a tiny creature.

440
00:30:25,557 --> 00:30:27,059
Spirit:
She died a woman

441
00:30:27,093 --> 00:30:29,561
and had, as I
recall, a child.

442
00:30:29,595 --> 00:30:32,164
Yes. My nephew Fred.

443
00:30:32,198 --> 00:30:35,868
Good-bye,
you wretched old school!

444
00:30:35,902 --> 00:30:36,936
Fan was right.

445
00:30:36,969 --> 00:30:41,607
We had
a happy Christmas
in spite of father.

446
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:45,444
Oh, I wish she were
alive to invite me
home again.

447
00:30:45,477 --> 00:30:49,248
But she has,
through her son Fred.

448
00:30:49,281 --> 00:30:50,983
Don't you see?

449
00:30:51,017 --> 00:30:53,485
Her goodness
lives in him.

450
00:30:53,519 --> 00:30:57,023
Yes. Oh, I wish...

451
00:30:57,056 --> 00:30:59,158
[growls]

452
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:00,559
Bah! Never mind!

453
00:31:00,592 --> 00:31:04,596
Let us visit
another kind soul.

454
00:31:15,041 --> 00:31:18,377
Why, it's old
Fezziwig, my boss.

455
00:31:18,410 --> 00:31:22,548
Bust my buttons!
He hasn't changed a bit.

456
00:31:23,015 --> 00:31:26,919
Ho ho there,
Ebenezer. Dick!

457
00:31:26,953 --> 00:31:28,587
No more
work tonight.

458
00:31:28,620 --> 00:31:31,958
No, no, it's
Christmas eve, my boys.

459
00:31:31,991 --> 00:31:36,963
Clear away, and let's
have lots of room here.

460
00:31:39,265 --> 00:31:43,269
I was
an apprentice here,
a good one, too.

461
00:31:43,302 --> 00:31:46,973
Old Fezziwig treated me
like his own son.

462
00:31:47,006 --> 00:31:49,008
[whimpers]

463
00:31:54,146 --> 00:31:56,983
[violin playing]

464
00:31:57,016 --> 00:31:59,918
Ha ha ha!

465
00:32:59,178 --> 00:33:00,779
Good old Fezziwig.

466
00:33:00,812 --> 00:33:03,682
Show me a better boss
than that, eh?

467
00:33:03,715 --> 00:33:07,753
So he spent a bit
of cash on some
song and dance.

468
00:33:07,786 --> 00:33:10,089
Where's the prize
in that, eh?

469
00:33:10,122 --> 00:33:11,290
Bit of coin?

470
00:33:11,323 --> 00:33:14,693
You couldn't buy
that much happiness
with a fortune.

471
00:33:14,726 --> 00:33:18,330
He had the power
to render us
happy or sad,

472
00:33:18,364 --> 00:33:21,600
to make our jobs
a pleasure
or a drudgery.

473
00:33:21,633 --> 00:33:27,339
Then he must have set
quite an example for you.

474
00:33:27,373 --> 00:33:28,807
Now what?

475
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:30,142
Oh, nothing particular.

476
00:33:30,176 --> 00:33:36,415
I'd like to be able
to say something to
Bob Cratchit just now.

477
00:33:36,448 --> 00:33:37,549
That's all.

478
00:33:37,583 --> 00:33:41,553
Come. My time
grows short.

479
00:33:51,397 --> 00:33:53,465
It's belle.

480
00:33:53,499 --> 00:33:57,203
Good news, my darling!
Guess what I've got.

481
00:33:57,236 --> 00:33:59,605
Give me a hint, Ebenezer.

482
00:33:59,638 --> 00:34:03,475
It's small
and round and gold,

483
00:34:03,509 --> 00:34:05,244
and it holds
the future.

484
00:34:05,277 --> 00:34:06,378
A ring?

485
00:34:06,412 --> 00:34:09,848
No! The profits
from my first
business venture!

486
00:34:09,881 --> 00:34:11,817
Isn't it wonderful,
belle?

487
00:34:11,850 --> 00:34:14,253
Now I'm sure
to be a success.

488
00:34:14,286 --> 00:34:18,056
Stop talking,
you mindless pup!

489
00:34:19,225 --> 00:34:22,394
Belle?

490
00:34:24,630 --> 00:34:29,535
* Now we've reached
this bridge together *

491
00:34:29,568 --> 00:34:35,741
* But I hope
we'll soon be crossed *

492
00:34:35,774 --> 00:34:41,280
* So don't put a price
on paradise *

493
00:34:41,313 --> 00:34:46,318
* Or our paradise is lost

494
00:34:46,352 --> 00:34:50,522
* Any bridge
leads to disaster *

495
00:34:50,556 --> 00:34:54,793
* If its moorings
aren't secure *

496
00:34:54,826 --> 00:35:00,232
* Heaven won't provide
on the bridge's
dark side *

497
00:35:00,266 --> 00:35:05,571
* It's our wealth
which will endure *

498
00:35:05,604 --> 00:35:09,708
* I'll cross
this bridge with you *

499
00:35:09,741 --> 00:35:15,414
* I'll cross
 this bridge with you *

500
00:35:15,447 --> 00:35:19,718
* Show me the man
that I once knew *

501
00:35:19,751 --> 00:35:24,756
* And I'll cross
this bridge with you *

502
00:35:24,790 --> 00:35:29,395
* No one lives
on hopes and wishes *

503
00:35:29,428 --> 00:35:34,166
* Love alone
grows dry and cold *

504
00:35:34,200 --> 00:35:39,671
* But the sun
will shine on these
bright dreams of mine *

505
00:35:39,705 --> 00:35:44,776
* As upon
this coin of gold *

506
00:35:44,810 --> 00:35:48,714
* Can I cross
this bridge with you? *

507
00:35:48,747 --> 00:35:50,182
* I'm who I am

508
00:35:50,216 --> 00:35:52,851
* Your words leave me
split in two *

509
00:35:52,884 --> 00:35:54,653
* What else can I do?

510
00:35:54,686 --> 00:35:58,757
* Has love begun
or is it through? *

511
00:35:58,790 --> 00:36:04,796
* Should I cross
this bridge with you? *

512
00:36:04,830 --> 00:36:07,966
* Life's so rocky
and unanswered *

513
00:36:07,999 --> 00:36:09,901
* And coarse to judge

514
00:36:09,935 --> 00:36:12,304
* Speak of love
so love can start *

515
00:36:12,338 --> 00:36:14,840
* Why not be safe
and smug? *

516
00:36:14,873 --> 00:36:16,808
* Where's your passion?
Where's your heart? *

517
00:36:16,842 --> 00:36:20,846
* Now it's time to say good-bye
to frivolous dreams we know *

518
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:33,425
* Can't we cross
this bridge together? *

519
00:36:33,459 --> 00:36:38,864
* I'll cross
this bridge *

520
00:36:38,897 --> 00:36:41,900
* Alone

521
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:51,510
Go after her,
you fool.

522
00:36:51,543 --> 00:36:53,211
[throws coin]

523
00:36:55,547 --> 00:36:56,848
Stop.

524
00:36:56,882 --> 00:36:58,917
Don't show me
any more.

525
00:36:58,950 --> 00:37:00,051
I told you.

526
