slushy stains to boot *

773
00:50:54,719 --> 00:50:57,655
* With the black
and beaten britches of
a big and burly brute *

774
00:50:57,688 --> 00:51:00,625
* Oh, there ne'er were duds
more in need of suds
than Santa's-- *

775
00:51:00,658 --> 00:51:01,859
* It had blotchy,
brownish buckles *

776
00:51:01,892 --> 00:51:03,027
* And a belt
of liquorice root *

777
00:51:03,060 --> 00:51:06,597
* With scruffy, fluffy ruffles
fallen into disrepute *

778
00:51:06,631 --> 00:51:08,133
* It was smudgy,
soiled, and sullied *

779
00:51:08,166 --> 00:51:09,134
* Yet somehow sort of cute

780
00:51:09,167 --> 00:51:10,768
* Never dreamed I might
see such a fright *

781
00:51:10,801 --> 00:51:12,603
* That made that night
when I looked right *

782
00:51:12,637 --> 00:51:14,272
* At Santa's stinky,
grey, and inky *

783
00:51:14,305 --> 00:51:15,706
* Messy, mucky, icky, yucky

784
00:51:15,740 --> 00:51:17,575
* Crunchy, grubby,
needs a scrubby *

785
00:51:17,608 --> 00:51:19,210
* Scrub-a-dub sooty suit!

786
00:51:19,244 --> 00:51:20,211
Hooray!

787
00:51:20,245 --> 00:51:23,248
Ha ha ha!

788
00:51:23,281 --> 00:51:24,782
Ha ha ha!

789
00:51:24,815 --> 00:51:26,484
Ha ha ha!

790
00:51:26,517 --> 00:51:28,586
Did you see me,
spirit?

791
00:51:28,619 --> 00:51:32,323
Ha ha ha!

792
00:51:32,357 --> 00:51:35,160
Yes, Scrooge.
Very merry.

793
00:51:35,193 --> 00:51:36,861
However, we must go now.

794
00:51:36,894 --> 00:51:38,863
But I was just
enjoying myself.

795
00:51:38,896 --> 00:51:44,735
Scrooge, my stay upon
this earth is very brief.

796
00:51:44,769 --> 00:51:46,771
It ends this very night.

797
00:51:46,804 --> 00:51:50,608
[chiming]

798
00:51:50,641 --> 00:51:54,679
Are spirits' lives
so short?

799
00:51:54,712 --> 00:51:55,780
Farewell.

800
00:51:55,813 --> 00:52:00,318
Farewell,
Ebenezer Scrooge.

801
00:52:03,354 --> 00:52:05,756
Spirit?

802
00:52:05,790 --> 00:52:08,159
[thunder]

803
00:52:08,193 --> 00:52:09,427
[gasp]

804
00:52:09,460 --> 00:52:11,696
Spirit?

805
00:52:13,698 --> 00:52:15,733
Spirit?

806
00:52:19,904 --> 00:52:23,341
Speak to me, spirit.

807
00:52:32,217 --> 00:52:33,818
[gasp]

808
00:52:34,752 --> 00:52:37,388
Am I correct that you are

809
00:52:37,422 --> 00:52:40,791
the ghost of Christmas
yet to come?

810
00:52:42,360 --> 00:52:44,729
Will you not speak
to me?

811
00:52:44,762 --> 00:52:47,665
Is it you who will
show me shadows

812
00:52:47,698 --> 00:52:51,736
of the things that
have not yet happened?

813
00:52:54,539 --> 00:53:00,578
Ghost of the future,
I fear you most of all.

814
00:53:00,611 --> 00:53:03,614
But if your goal
is to do me good,

815
00:53:03,648 --> 00:53:07,785
then I hope to be
a better person than before.

816
00:53:08,753 --> 00:53:11,356
Lead on.

817
00:53:16,727 --> 00:53:19,797
This is
the business exchange.

818
00:53:19,830 --> 00:53:22,633
I come here often.

819
00:53:22,667 --> 00:53:25,703
But where am I today?

820
00:53:26,671 --> 00:53:29,574
No, I don't know much
about it either way.

821
00:53:29,607 --> 00:53:31,409
I only know he died
last night.

822
00:53:31,442 --> 00:53:34,512
Well, the devil has got
his own at last, eh?

823
00:53:34,545 --> 00:53:36,247
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

824
00:53:36,281 --> 00:53:37,582
What's he done
with his money?

825
00:53:37,615 --> 00:53:41,018
Oh, he hasn't
left it to me.
That's all I know.

826
00:53:41,051 --> 00:53:45,623
Gentlemen, tell me,
which of our colleagues
has died?

827
00:53:45,656 --> 00:53:47,725
It will probably be
a cheap funeral

828
00:53:47,758 --> 00:53:49,660
'cause nobody
will go to it.

829
00:53:49,694 --> 00:53:51,262
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

830
00:53:51,296 --> 00:53:54,932
Oh, I don't mind
going if a lunch
is provided.

831
00:53:54,965 --> 00:53:57,468
Well, good day.

832
00:53:58,503 --> 00:54:01,672
Spirit, I don't understand
the meaning of this.

833
00:54:01,706 --> 00:54:04,809
Who has died?

834
00:54:31,001 --> 00:54:32,703
Yaaah!

835
00:54:34,505 --> 00:54:38,576
Woman: Oh,
look what I found
under here.

836
00:54:38,609 --> 00:54:40,611
Silver, they are.

837
00:54:40,645 --> 00:54:42,713
Think he'll miss 'em?

838
00:54:42,747 --> 00:54:43,748
Nah.

839
00:54:43,781 --> 00:54:45,983
His tea-stirring days
are over.

840
00:54:46,016 --> 00:54:47,985
Ha ha ha ha!

841
00:54:48,018 --> 00:54:48,986
If he wanted someone

842
00:54:49,019 --> 00:54:52,089
to look after
his belongings
after he was dead,

843
00:54:52,122 --> 00:54:55,693
he should have
made friends when he
was still breathing.

844
00:54:55,726 --> 00:55:01,065
Aye, love,
truer words
was never spoke.

845
00:55:01,666 --> 00:55:05,503
You don't mean
to take 'em with
him lyin' there?

846
00:55:05,536 --> 00:55:06,504
Why not?

847
00:55:06,537 --> 00:55:09,707
It's not like he's
gonna catch cold
without 'em.

848
00:55:09,740 --> 00:55:12,543
Or without his
bed curtains,
either.

849
00:55:12,577 --> 00:55:13,978
[both laughing]

850
00:55:14,011 --> 00:55:15,846
[coughing]

851
00:55:16,714 --> 00:55:18,483
Spirit...

852
00:55:18,516 --> 00:55:20,951
This is
a fearful place.

853
00:55:20,985 --> 00:55:23,388
But I see
the lesson.

854
00:55:23,421 --> 00:55:25,756
The fate of
this unhappy man

855
00:55:25,790 --> 00:55:29,126
might happen
to me someday...

856
00:55:29,159 --> 00:55:31,429
Right?

857
00:55:33,398 --> 00:55:35,633
Oh, this is
too harsh to bear.

858
00:55:35,666 --> 00:55:40,004
Let me see some
tenderness connected
with the death,

859
00:55:40,037 --> 00:55:42,440
I beseech you.

860
00:55:50,080 --> 00:55:52,683
[woman sobbing]

861
00:55:52,717 --> 00:55:55,720
Oh, the lamp
is so bright
it hurts my eyes.

862
00:55:55,753 --> 00:55:59,690
I mustn't show
weak eyes to your father
when he comes home.

863
00:55:59,724 --> 00:56:00,991
It must be
near his time.

864
00:56:01,025 --> 00:56:02,226
Past it.

865
00:56:02,259 --> 00:56:05,896
I think he walks
a little slower than
he used to, mother.

866
00:56:05,930 --> 00:56:08,666
Oh, I have known him
to walk with...

867
00:56:08,699 --> 00:56:12,470
With tiny Tim
upon his shoulder
very fast indeed.

868
00:56:12,503 --> 00:56:17,007
But he was very light
to carry, and no trouble.

869
00:56:17,041 --> 00:56:18,008
[sighs]

870
00:56:18,042 --> 00:56:18,976
No trouble.

871
00:56:19,009 --> 00:56:19,977
[door opens]

872
00:56:20,010 --> 00:56:21,045
Bob: Sorry I'm late.

873
00:56:21,078 --> 00:56:22,980
You went there
today, robert?

874
00:56:23,013 --> 00:56:23,981
Yes, dear.

875
00:56:24,014 --> 00:56:25,683
I wish you all
could have gone.

876
00:56:25,716 --> 00:56:28,786
You would have enjoyed
seeing how green
a place it is.

877
00:56:28,819 --> 00:56:32,723
I promised him
that I would walk
there on sunday.

878
00:56:32,757 --> 00:56:33,724
[sobbing]

879
00:56:33,758 --> 00:56:35,726
Little boy...

880
00:56:35,760 --> 00:56:37,695
My little boy...

881
00:56:37,728 --> 00:56:39,797
[sobbing]

882
00:56:42,533 --> 00:56:44,034
No, spectre, no!

883
00:56:44,068 --> 00:56:47,838
Not--not tiny Tim.

884
00:56:51,742 --> 00:56:53,678
Spirit, tell me...

885
00:56:53,711 --> 00:56:59,016
Can this cruel future
be changed?

886
00:57:07,758 --> 00:57:09,527
Scrooge:
Is this, then,

887
00:57:09,560 --> 00:57:14,965
where that wretched dead man
now lies underground?

888
00:57:27,545 --> 00:57:29,780
Before I look closer,

889
00:57:29,814 --> 00:57:31,081
answer me one question:

890
00:57:31,115 --> 00:57:34,952
Are these the shadows
of the things that will be

891
00:57:34,985 --> 00:57:39,223
or only the things
that might be?

892
00:57:39,824 --> 00:57:42,893
All lives lead
to certain ends,

893
00:57:42,927 --> 00:57:44,895
but if our lives change,

894
00:57:44,929 --> 00:57:48,666
then the ends must
also change, right?

895
00:57:48,699 --> 00:57:50,701
They must!

896
00:57:51,736 --> 00:57:54,238
[breathing shakily]

897
00:57:59,544 --> 00:58:00,645
[gasps]

898
00:58:00,678 --> 00:58:01,946
No.

899
00:58:05,783 --> 00:58:06,751
No!

900
00:58:06,784 --> 00:58:07,752
[gasps]

901
00:58:07,785 --> 00:58:11,188
That lonely corpse
was me!

902
00:58:11,221 --> 00:58:12,256
Oh, no.

903
00:58:12,289 --> 00:58:13,691
[sobbing]

904
00:58:13,724 --> 00:58:14,692
No.

905
00:58:14,725 --> 00:58:17,995
Don't let me
die unmourned.

906
00:58:18,028 --> 00:58:20,030
Spirit, listen.

907
00:58:20,064 --> 00:58:23,167
I am not
the man I was.

908
00:58:23,200 --> 00:58:24,669
I've changed.

909
00:58:24,702 --> 00:58:27,705
I will honor Christmas
in my heart

910
00:58:27,738 --> 00:58:30,040
and keep it all the year.

911
00:58:30,074 --> 00:58:32,209
I will learn
from the past,

912
00:58:32,242 --> 00:58:34,679
I will live
 in the present,

913
00:58:34,712 --> 00:58:37,982
and I will hope
 for the future.

914
00:58:38,015 --> 00:58:41,586
I will keep
the 3 spirits in my soul

915
00:58:41,619 --> 00:58:45,623
and remember
their lessons always.

916
00:58:49,694 --> 00:58:51,195
Good spirit,

917
00:58:51,228 --> 00:58:54,031
I'm not that man anymore.

918
00:58:54,064 --> 00:58:58,803
Why show me these shadows
if I am past all hope?

919
00:58:58,836 --> 00:59:05,209
Please tell me that
I can make a brighter
future than this.

920
00:59:14,051 --> 00:59:16,887
All alone.

921
00:59:19,056 --> 00:59:20,925
Stranded.

922
00:59:31,802 --> 00:59:33,203
[gasps]

923
00:59:34,004 --> 00:59:35,906
I'm home?

924
00:59:35,940 --> 00:59:39,610
I'm home!

925
00:59:39,644 --> 00:59:41,879
[snoring]

926
00:59:41,912 --> 00:59:45,750
I'm home!

927
00:59:45,783 --> 00:59:48,619
I've been given
another chance, debit,

928
00:59:48,653 --> 00:59:50,320
and so have you.

929
00:59:50,354 --> 00:59:51,722
Mmm-uhh!

930
00:59:51,756 --> 00:59:53,758
Oh, ha ha ha!

931
00:59:53,791 --> 00:59:57,194
Ha ha ha!

932
00:59:57,227 --> 01:00:00,998
Oh, heaven and
Christmastime be praised.

933
01:00:01,031 --> 01:00:04,735
I say it on my knees,
old Jacob.

934
01:00:04,769 --> 01:00:06,804
On my knees!

935
01:00:06,837 --> 01:00:09,173
Ha ha ha ha ha!

936
01:00:14,979 --> 01:00:16,814
My spoons!

937
01:00:16,847 --> 01:00:19,249
They're still here.

938
01:00:23,087 --> 01:00:26,857
The dark shadows of things
that would have been...

939
01:00:26,891 --> 01:00:28,258
Are gone.

940
01:00:28,292 --> 01:00:30,795
I know they are.

941
01:00:31,095 --> 01:00:34,331
* I heard a tale
about Christmas *

942
01:00:34,364 --> 01:00:37,802
* Whose truth
caused my spirit to burn *

943
01:00:37,835 --> 01:00:42,673
* My present, my past,
and my future *

944
01:00:42,707 --> 01:00:45,943
* Taught me
I'd so much to learn *

945
01:00:45,976 --> 01:00:49,346
* I've lived a tale
of a miser *

946
01:00:49,379 --> 01:00:53,017
* Who spoiled every joy
that he could *

947
01:00:53,050 --> 01:00:56,821
* Then he got older
and wiser *

948
01:00:56,854 --> 01:00:59,456
* And only yearned
to be good *

949
01:00:59,489 --> 01:01:02,259
* Once my memories

950
01:01:02,292 --> 01:01:05,696
* Brought me
nothing but pain *

951
01:01:05,730 --> 01:01:08,699
* Now it's Christmas

952
01:01:08,733 --> 01:01:10,935
* With new precious memories
to gain *

953
01:01:10,968 --> 01:01:13,437
* I'll sing a song
full of wonder *

954
01:01:13,470 --> 01:01:16,340
* Like snow
from the heavens above *

955
01:01:16,373 --> 01:01:19,777
* I'll share my new song
of Christmas *

956
01:01:19,810 --> 01:01:20,778
Ha ha ha ha!

957
01:01:20,811 --> 01:01:24,815
* I've a new song
of love *

958
01:01:36,526 --> 01:01:38,896
A merry Christmas
to everybody!

959
01:01:38,929 --> 01:01:43,801
Happy new year
to the world!

960
01:01:43,834 --> 01:01:46,904
Hello,
my fine fellow.

961
01:01:46,937 --> 01:01:48,105
Huh?

962
01:01:48,138 --> 01:01:49,439
Yes, you, lad!

963
01:01:49,473 --> 01:01:51,075
[whimpering]

964
01:01:51,108 --> 01:01:53,410
Wait. Don't run.

965
01:01:53,443 --> 01:01:54,478
Please.

966
01:01:54,511 --> 01:01:56,881
But what is it, then?

967
01:01:56,914 --> 01:02:00,184
Do you know
the poultry shop
down the street?

968
01:02:00,217 --> 01:02:02,086
Ha! Is snow white?

969
01:02:02,119 --> 01:02:03,954
An intelligent boy.

970
01:02:03,988 --> 01:02:06,090
A remarkable boy.

971
01:02:06,123 --> 01:02:08,525
Do you know
whether they've sold

972
01:02:08,558 --> 01:02:11,195
the prize turkey
that was hanging there?

973
01:02:11,228 --> 01:02:13,530
What? The one
as big as me?

974
01:02:13,563 --> 01:02:16,767
Ha ha ha!
Yes, my lad.
That very one.

975
01:02:16,801 --> 01:02:22,106
Tell 'em to bring it
here, and I'll give you
a silver coin.

976
01:02:22,139 --> 01:02:23,140
Do you mean it?

977
01:02:23,173 --> 01:02:24,341
Aye, lad.

978
01:02:24,374 --> 01:02:29,546
Come back in less
than 5 minutes,
and I'll give you 2.

979
01:02:29,579 --> 01:02:31,849
Ha ha ha ha!

980
01:02:32,482 --> 01:02:37,788
Come, my faithful friend,
we have much to do.

981
01:02:39,556 --> 01:02:41,792
[panting]

982
01:02:48,332 --> 01:02:50,968
Merry Christmas,
gentlemen!

983
01:02:51,001 --> 01:02:53,203
And a happy new year!

984
01:02:53,237 --> 01:02:55,405
[men gasp]

985
01:02:57,441 --> 01:02:59,409
Oh, dear.

986
01:03:01,879 --> 01:03:03,547
[both gasp]

987
01:03:04,849 --> 01:03:05,983
Scrooge: No!

988
01:03:06,016 --> 01:03:08,018
Wait. Come back!

989
01:03:08,052 --> 01:03:10,154
[growling]

990
01:03:14,458 --> 01:03:17,561
We won't pester you
for money ever again!

991
01:03:17,594 --> 01:03:18,562
We promise!

992
01:03:18,595 --> 01:03:20,030
No, no. Please.

993
01:03:20,064 --> 01:03:21,565
I must apologize
to you both

994
01:03:21,598 --> 01:03:24,601
for the terrible way
I treated you yesterday.

995
01:03:24,634 --> 01:03:28,505
You are  Mr. Scrooge,
 aren't you?

996
01:03:28,538 --> 01:03:32,209
Well, not
that old Scrooge,
at any rate.

997
01:03:32,242 --> 01:03:35,345
Please, let me
donate something

998
01:03:35,379 --> 01:03:40,150
to...To make up
for my selfishness.

999
01:03:40,184 --> 01:03:42,552
Well, certainly.

1000
01:03:42,586 --> 01:03:46,590
So you'll come see me
tomorrow at my office?

1001
01:03:46,623 --> 01:03:50,227
Most certainly.
But, Mr. Scrooge,

1002
01:03:50,260 --> 01:03:51,261
why now?

1003
01:03:51,295 --> 01:03:56,066
Because it's too late
to do it when we're dead.

1004
01:03:56,100 --> 01:03:57,534
Ah!
Ah!

1005
01:03:57,567 --> 01:03:59,269
Yes.
Yes, of course.

1006
01:03:59,303 --> 01:04:01,005
Thank you.
Thank you, Mr. Scrooge.

1007
01:04:01,038 --> 01:04:03,607
Thank you, 
 gentlemen.

1008
01:04:03,640 --> 01:04:06,543
Ha ha ha ha!

1009
01:04:06,576 --> 01:04:10,214
You know, debit,
I like this feeling,

1010
01:04:10,247 --> 01:04:15,019
though I'm not used to
all this smiling yet.

1011
01:04:15,052 --> 01:04:18,555
Bob: Well, my dears,
we may truly count
our blessings.

1012
01:04:18,588 --> 01:04:23,493
I have no idea where this
magnificent bird came from,

1013
01:04:23,527 --> 01:04:24,494
but let's eat!

1014
01:04:24,528 --> 01:04:26,130
Yay!
Let's eat!
Let's!

1015
01:04:26,163 --> 01:04:27,631
[knock at door]

1016
01:04:27,664 --> 01:04:29,599
Oh!

1017
01:04:33,938 --> 01:04:35,239
Merry Christmas!

1018
01:04:35,272 --> 01:04:37,674
Uh, merry Christmas
to you.

1019
01:04:37,707 --> 01:04:40,644
Darling, this is
Mr. Scrooge's nephew,

1020
01:04:40,677 --> 01:04:41,645
master Fred.

1021
01:04:41,678 --> 01:04:44,348
And my dear wife.
May we come in?

1022
01:04:44,381 --> 01:04:47,084
Oh, forgive me.
Of course.

1023
01:04:47,117 --> 01:04:48,052
Please join us.

1024
01:04:48,085 --> 01:04:51,355
We received word
to meet Uncle Ebenezer
here.

1025
01:04:51,388 --> 01:04:52,589
Very urgent.

1026
01:04:52,622 --> 01:04:55,592
Mr. Scrooge?
Coming here?

1027
01:04:55,625 --> 01:04:58,095
What have I done now?

1028
01:04:58,128 --> 01:04:58,895
Hee hee hee!

1029
01:04:58,929 --> 01:05:02,599
Won't Bob Cratchit
be surprised?

1030
01:05:03,267 --> 01:05:04,901
How's this?

1031
01:05:05,602 --> 01:05:06,470
[panting]

1032
01:05:06,503 --> 01:05:10,374
No, no.
You must look mean
as well.

1033
01:05:16,546 --> 01:05:19,483
Debit! Nasty!

1034
01:05:20,250 --> 01:05:21,218
Oh!

1035
01:05:21,251 --> 01:05:22,552
[growling]

1036
01:05:22,586 --> 01:05:24,621
Good, good.

1037
01:05:31,661 --> 01:05:34,131
Cratchit.

1038
01:05:34,164 --> 01:05:36,600
M--Mr. Scrooge?

1039
01:05:36,633 --> 01:05:40,137
What do you mean
being here
this time of day?

1040
01:05:40,170 --> 01:05:41,371
I--i--i--it's...

1041
01:05:41,405 --> 01:05:43,707
Only once a year, sir.

1042
01:05:43,740 --> 01:05:44,708
Uncle!

1043
01:05:44,741 --> 01:05:46,643
[debit growling]

1044
01:05:46,676 --> 01:05:47,944
Uh!

1045
01:05:47,978 --> 01:05:52,116
I am not going to stand
for this sort of thing
any longer,

1046
01:05:52,149 --> 01:05:55,452
and therefore,
I am about to...

1047
01:05:55,485 --> 01:05:57,621
No, please,
Mr. Scrooge...

1048
01:05:57,654 --> 01:06:01,225
Raise your salary.

1049
01:06:01,258 --> 01:06:02,559
Huh!

1050
01:06:02,592 --> 01:06:03,994
A raise?

1051
01:06:04,028 --> 01:06:05,095
A raise!

1052
01:06:05,129 --> 01:06:08,765
A merry Christmas,
bob.

1053
01:06:08,798 --> 01:06:10,234
[ruff]

1054
01:06:10,267 --> 01:06:11,068
Scrooge: Yes!

1055
01:06:11,101 --> 01:06:14,538
A merrier Christmas,
my good fellow,

1056
01:06:14,571 --> 01:06:18,508
than I have given
you for many a year.

1057
01:06:18,542 --> 01:06:20,410
And starting today,

1058
01:06:20,444 --> 01:06:23,613
I'm paying you
what you deserve.

1059
01:06:23,647 --> 01:06:25,082
[children cheering]

1060
01:06:25,115 --> 01:06:26,583
I, uh...

1061
01:06:26,616 --> 01:06:27,584
I--

1062
01:06:27,617 --> 01:06:30,120
I give you
Mr. Scrooge,

1063
01:06:30,154 --> 01:06:32,556
the founder
of the feast.

1064
01:06:32,589 --> 01:06:33,790
All: Hear, hear!

1065
01:06:33,823 --> 01:06:35,659
[all laughing]

1066
01:06:37,227 --> 01:06:39,263
[ruff ruff]

1067
01:06:42,332 --> 01:06:44,634
[playing lively tune]

1068
01:06:50,807 --> 01:06:53,310
[children laughing]

1069
01:06:53,343 --> 01:06:54,378
Scrooge: Yes!

1070
01:06:54,411 --> 01:06:56,146
Just like
at old Fezziwig's.

1071
01:06:56,180 --> 01:07:01,418
And later, Fred
 and I will teach you
 Santa's sooty suit.

1072
01:07:01,451 --> 01:07:03,320
[children cheering]

1073
01:07:03,353 --> 01:07:04,588
We will, indeed.

1074
01:07:04,621 --> 01:07:08,192
Now let's celebrate!

1075
01:07:08,225 --> 01:07:11,195
Oh, a dolly!

1076
01:07:16,766 --> 01:07:18,135
Fred, my boy,

1077
01:07:18,168 --> 01:07:21,571
is there enough
of your mother in you

1078
01:07:21,605 --> 01:07:24,441
to forgive
an old humbug?

1079
01:07:24,474 --> 01:07:28,112
Welcome to the family,
Uncle Scrooge.

1080
01:07:31,481 --> 01:07:33,417
Do you like it, Tim?

1081
01:07:33,450 --> 01:07:36,620
Oh, yes, sir!
Thank you, sir!

1082
01:07:36,653 --> 01:07:39,289
We're going to
get you well,
young man.

1083
01:07:39,323 --> 01:07:44,328
And afterward,
you can teach me
to slide on the ice.

1084
01:07:44,361 --> 01:07:45,662
Oh, yes, sir!

1085
01:07:45,695 --> 01:07:47,464
And the doggy, too.

1086
01:07:47,497 --> 01:07:48,732
God bless us.

1087
01:07:48,765 --> 01:07:53,203
Both: God bless us,
every one.

1088
01:07:53,237 --> 01:07:54,804
[ruff ruff]

1089
01:07:54,838 --> 01:07:58,542
Narrator: And Scrooge
was as good as his word.

1090
01:07:58,575 --> 01:07:59,643
No, better.

1091
01:07:59,676 --> 01:08:01,678
He was like
a second father to Tim

1092
01:08:01,711 --> 01:08:04,514
and became as good a friend,
as good a master,

1093
01:08:04,548 --> 01:08:08,452
and as good a man
as anyone in the world.

1094
01:08:08,485 --> 01:08:13,423
And he kept Christmas
in his heart forever.

